---
import Robot from './svelte/Robot/index.svelte';
import CTA from './svelte/CTA/index.svelte';
---

<div class="bg-white py-24 sm:py-32">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div
      class="mx-auto grid max-w-2xl grid-cols-1 items-start gap-x-8 gap-y-16 sm:gap-y-24 lg:mx-0 lg:max-w-none lg:grid-cols-2"
    >
      <div class="lg:pr-4">
        <Robot client:load />
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="text-base leading-7 text-gray-700 lg:max-w-lg">
          <p
            class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight bg-brand-green w-fit p-1"
          >
            Our values
          </p>
          <h1
            class="mt-2 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-4xl"
          >
            On a mission to make a more fun, accessible web
          </h1>
          <div class="max-w-xl">
            <p class="mt-6">
              We at Hackitude are head-over-heels in love with the
              infinite possibilities of the web. In fact, we're so
              smitten that we've dedicated our lives to exploring
              every nook and cranny of web development, UX design, and
              accessibility.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-8">
              We believe that the world wide web is like the world's
              biggest playground. It's a place where ideas take shape,
              creativity blossoms, and the impossible becomes
              possible. We're the kids who never stopped playing in
              this sandbox, building digital sandcastles with code,
              user experience, and inclusive design.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-8">
              As champions of equity, we're committed to making the
              internet a place for everyone. We understand that a
              truly fantastic website is not just about flashy designs
              and complex functionalitiesâ€”it's about ensuring every
              individual, regardless of their abilities or
              disabilities, can navigate, interact, and enjoy the
              online experience. And we aim to spread this ethos
              through everything we do at Hackitude.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-8">
              Come join us at Hackitude and let's play, learn, and
              grow together in this wonderfully weird, wild, and wacky
              web world!
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-10">
          <CTA
            client:load
            url="/resources"
            text="Learn about development"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
